# Finding-adjudication golden set — audit PRECISION (false-positive resistance).
# Every other audit eval in this harness measures RECALL (does it find the real vuln?)
# and saturates at +0.00. This one measures the opposite failure: does the auditor
# UPHOLD a plausible-but-wrong finding? That is what an adversarial refutation pass
# (sota/rules/01-audit-methodology.md §6) is supposed to prevent.
#
# Each case = a code snippet + a CLAIMED finding. expect is ["UPHELD"] (the claim
# holds) or ["REFUTED"] (it does not). 15 of each. The REFUTED half fails for six
# distinct reasons — upstream guard, unreachable code, inflated severity, misread
# mechanism, already-mitigated, and behaviour that is actually correct — so an arm
# cannot win by pattern-matching one refutation shape.
# `why` is the answer key (never prompted). `reason` tags the refutation class.
{"id": "fa01", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "q = \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = '\" + request.args[\"email\"] + \"'\"\nrows = db.execute(q)", "claim": "SQL injection (Critical): request.args['email'] is concatenated into the query.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "String concatenation of unvalidated request data straight into SQL. Real, Critical."}
{"id": "fa02", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "def get_invoice(invoice_id: int, user):\n    inv = db.query(Invoice).filter(Invoice.id == invoice_id).first()\n    return inv.to_dict()", "claim": "IDOR (High): no ownership predicate — any authenticated caller reads any invoice.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "The query filters on id only; no tenant/owner predicate anywhere in the path. Real IDOR."}
{"id": "fa03", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "go", "snippet": "func Auth(tok string) bool {\n\tok, err := verify(tok)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\treturn ok\n}", "claim": "Fail-open authentication (Critical): a verification error returns true.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "The error branch returns true (authenticated). Real fail-open on the auth path."}
{"id": "fa04", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "if hmac_from_header == computed_hmac:\n    process(payload)", "claim": "Non-constant-time comparison (Medium): signature compared with ==.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "== on a secret-derived value is timing-variable; hmac.compare_digest is required."}
{"id": "fa05", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "javascript", "snippet": "app.get(\"/fetch\", async (req, res) => {\n  const r = await fetch(req.query.url);\n  res.send(await r.text());\n});", "claim": "SSRF (High): the client controls the fetched URL with no validation.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "req.query.url reaches fetch with no scheme allowlist or private-IP block. Real SSRF."}
{"id": "fa06", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "data = pickle.loads(base64.b64decode(request.form[\"state\"]))", "claim": "Unsafe deserialization (Critical): pickle.loads on client-supplied data.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "pickle.loads on attacker-controlled bytes is RCE. Real, Critical."}
{"id": "fa07", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "user = User(**request.get_json())\ndb.add(user)", "claim": "Mass assignment (High): posted JSON can set any column, including is_admin.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "Unfiltered **kwargs from the request body into the model constructor. Real."}
{"id": "fa08", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "path = os.path.join(UPLOAD_DIR, request.args[\"name\"])\nreturn send_file(path)", "claim": "Path traversal (High): the filename is not canonicalized.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "'../' in name escapes UPLOAD_DIR; os.path.join does not constrain. Real traversal."}
{"id": "fa09", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "token = \"\".join(random.choice(string.ascii_letters) for _ in range(16))\nsend_reset_link(token)", "claim": "Insecure randomness (High): password-reset token from the random module.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "random is a Mersenne Twister, predictable from observed outputs. Real for a reset token."}
{"id": "fa10", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "yaml", "snippet": "apiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: app\n    image: app:latest\n    securityContext:\n      privileged: true", "claim": "Privileged container (High): privileged: true grants full host device access.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "privileged: true disables most container isolation. Real, and no compensating control shown."}
{"id": "fa11", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "@app.route(\"/admin/users\")\ndef admin_users():\n    return jsonify([u.to_dict() for u in User.query.all()])", "claim": "Missing authorization (Critical): an admin route with no authn/authz decorator.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "No decorator, no in-body check; the route is registered and returns all users. Real."}
{"id": "fa12", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "javascript", "snippet": "res.setHeader(\"Access-Control-Allow-Origin\", req.headers.origin);\nres.setHeader(\"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials\", \"true\");", "claim": "CORS misconfiguration (Critical): origin reflected with credentials allowed.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "Reflecting Origin while allowing credentials lets any site read authenticated responses. Real."}
{"id": "fa13", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "cipher = AES.new(key, AES.MODE_ECB)\nct = cipher.encrypt(pad(plaintext, 16))", "claim": "Weak cipher mode (Medium): ECB leaks plaintext structure and is unauthenticated.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "ECB is deterministic per block and provides no integrity. Real crypto misuse."}
{"id": "fa14", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "logger.info(\"password reset for %s with token %s\", email, reset_token)", "claim": "Secret in logs (Medium): the reset token is written to the application log.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "A live credential is logged in plaintext; log readers gain account takeover. Real."}
{"id": "fa15", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "go", "snippet": "tr := &http.Transport{TLSClientConfig: &tls.Config{InsecureSkipVerify: true}}\nclient := &http.Client{Transport: tr}", "claim": "Disabled TLS verification (High): InsecureSkipVerify defeats certificate checking.", "expect": ["UPHELD"], "why": "InsecureSkipVerify: true accepts any certificate — MITM. Real, and no pinning replaces it."}
{"id": "fa16", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "ALLOWED = {\"name\", \"email\", \"created_at\"}\n\ndef search(request):\n    col = request.args[\"sort\"]\n    if col not in ALLOWED:\n        abort(400)\n    return db.execute(f\"SELECT * FROM users ORDER BY {col}\")", "claim": "SQL injection (Critical): request.args['sort'] is interpolated into the query with an f-string.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The value is checked against a fixed allowlist and rejected with abort(400) before it reaches the query, so only three literal column names can ever be interpolated. Identifier allowlisting is the correct pattern for a column name, which cannot be parameterized.", "reason": "upstream-guard"}
{"id": "fa17", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "def legacy_export(fmt):\n    return os.popen(f\"exporter --format {fmt}\").read()\n\n# no callers; module not imported anywhere; not registered as a route or CLI command", "claim": "Command injection (Critical): fmt is interpolated into a shell command.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The function has no callers and the module is imported nowhere, so no attacker-controlled input can reach it. It is dead code — real hardening debt at Low, but not a Critical exploitable finding as claimed.", "reason": "unreachable"}
{"id": "fa18", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "response.headers[\"X-Frame-Options\"] = \"SAMEORIGIN\"\n# no Strict-Transport-Security header is set; the app is served behind a TLS-terminating proxy that adds HSTS", "claim": "Authentication bypass (Critical): the application does not set Strict-Transport-Security.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "A missing HSTS header is a defense-in-depth hardening gap, not an authentication bypass, and the severity does not follow from the mechanism. It is also already set at the proxy. Low at most.", "reason": "inflated-severity"}
{"id": "fa19", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "import ast\nvalue = ast.literal_eval(request.form[\"payload\"])", "claim": "Arbitrary code execution (Critical): user input is evaluated.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "ast.literal_eval is not eval — it parses only Python literals (strings, numbers, tuples, lists, dicts, booleans, None) and raises ValueError on anything else, including function calls and attribute access. No code executes.", "reason": "misread-mechanism"}
{"id": "fa20", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "@rate_limit(\"5/minute\", key=lambda: request.remote_addr)\n@app.route(\"/login\", methods=[\"POST\"])\ndef login():\n    return do_login(request.form)", "claim": "Missing rate limit on login (Medium): the login endpoint has no brute-force protection.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "A rate_limit decorator of 5/minute keyed on the client address is applied directly to this handler. The control the finding says is absent is present in the snippet.", "reason": "already-mitigated"}
{"id": "fa21", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "go", "snippet": "func Authorize(p, r string) bool {\n\tallowed, err := policy.Check(p, r)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(\"policy check failed, denying\", \"err\", err)\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\treturn allowed\n}", "claim": "Fail-open authorization (Critical): the error path bypasses the policy engine.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The error path returns false, which denies. The function fails CLOSED and logs the failure. The claimed behaviour is the opposite of what the code does.", "reason": "correct-behaviour"}
{"id": "fa22", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "TEST_API_KEY = \"sk_test_EXAMPLE_PLACEHOLDER_NOT_A_REAL_KEY\"  # vendor-published test-mode key, tests/conftest.py", "claim": "Hardcoded secret (Critical): a live API key is committed to the repository.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "This is a vendor-published test-mode key in a test fixture — public by design, grants no access to real data, and cannot move money. Test-mode credentials are documented as shareable. Not a credential leak.", "reason": "misread-mechanism"}
{"id": "fa23", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "def render(tpl_name, ctx):\n    tpl = env.get_template(tpl_name)   # jinja2 Environment(autoescape=True)\n    return tpl.render(**ctx)", "claim": "XSS (High): user-supplied context is rendered into HTML without escaping.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The Jinja2 Environment is constructed with autoescape=True, so variables are HTML-escaped on render. Escaping is applied; the claim's premise is false.", "reason": "upstream-guard"}
{"id": "fa24", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "javascript", "snippet": "const id = Number(req.params.id);\nif (!Number.isInteger(id) || id < 1) return res.sendStatus(400);\nconst row = await db.query(\"SELECT * FROM posts WHERE id = $1 AND author_id = $2\", [id, req.user.id]);", "claim": "IDOR (High): the route takes an object id from the client.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The query is parameterized and carries an author_id predicate bound to the session user, so a caller cannot read another author's post. Taking an id from the client is not itself IDOR when ownership is enforced in the query.", "reason": "upstream-guard"}
{"id": "fa25", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "subprocess.run([\"git\", \"clone\", repo_url], check=True, timeout=60)", "claim": "Command injection (High): repo_url is passed to a subprocess.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The argv-list form is used with no shell=True, so repo_url is a single argv element and cannot introduce shell metacharacters. This is the recommended safe pattern.", "reason": "misread-mechanism"}
{"id": "fa26", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "def _debug_dump(obj):\n    return pickle.loads(obj)\n\n# called only from tests/test_pickle_roundtrip.py with locally-constructed bytes", "claim": "Unsafe deserialization (Critical): pickle.loads on untrusted input.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The only caller is a test that constructs the bytes locally; no request path reaches it. Worth removing as hardening debt, but not the Critical remote-code-execution finding claimed.", "reason": "unreachable"}
{"id": "fa27", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "cookie_opts = dict(httponly=True, samesite=\"Lax\", secure=True)\nresp.set_cookie(\"sid\", sid, **cookie_opts)", "claim": "Session fixation (High): the session cookie lacks security attributes.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The cookie is set with httponly, secure, and samesite=Lax. The attributes the finding says are missing are all present, and none of them concern fixation in any case.", "reason": "correct-behaviour"}
{"id": "fa28", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "hashed = bcrypt.hashpw(password.encode(), bcrypt.gensalt(rounds=12))", "claim": "Weak password hashing (High): bcrypt is obsolete and must be replaced with argon2id.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "bcrypt at cost 12 remains an acceptable password hash under current OWASP guidance; argon2id is preferred for new work but bcrypt is not a vulnerability. At most an Info-level modernization note.", "reason": "inflated-severity"}
{"id": "fa29", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "python", "snippet": "raw = request.get_data()\nif not hmac.compare_digest(sig_header, hmac.new(SECRET, raw, \"sha256\").hexdigest()):\n    abort(403)\nevent = json.loads(raw)", "claim": "Webhook signature bypass (Critical): the payload is parsed before the signature is checked.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "The comparison runs first and aborts with 403 on mismatch; json.loads is only reached after a constant-time signature check passes. The claimed ordering is reversed.", "reason": "correct-behaviour"}
{"id": "fa30", "kind": "adjudication", "language": "yaml", "snippet": "spec:\n  containers:\n  - name: app\n    image: registry.example.com/app@sha256:9f2c...\n    securityContext:\n      runAsNonRoot: true\n      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n      capabilities: {drop: [\"ALL\"]}", "claim": "Container runs as root (High): no user is specified for the container.", "expect": ["REFUTED"], "why": "runAsNonRoot: true is set, privilege escalation is disabled, and all capabilities are dropped. The kubelet refuses to start the pod if the image's user resolves to root, so the claimed condition cannot occur.", "reason": "correct-behaviour"}
